reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My new favorite contour!
reviews.reviewText: This is my new go-to product for contouring! I absolutely love the texture! It feels light and hydrating on the skin and blends like a dream. The formula is buildable for a more a dramatic look, but I would say a little goes a long way. The top swatch I took is a thick glob of the product so the color is more apparent, but the bottom one is just a few dots blended out a little bit with my finger.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Natural darker shading
reviews.reviewText: I use cream products because my face is dry. I really like this contour stick since it is blendable. The only area it struggled was my jaw, it was harder to blend. But the sides of my face were easy to mix.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Expecting more because people say that it’s the best for me…No
reviews.reviewText: I have purchased this several times -it does work well, but not amy favorite there are others that are in the drugstore category that work much better. I prefer a stick contour or blush because you are controlling the amount on your face more. I also don’t think the product stays on as long as the sticks. It is a product worth buying especially if you get it on sale. I gave it four stars because it’s not the holy Grail, but I was thinking it would be when I purchased it due to viral views. It might work for you a little better.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great contour stick
reviews.reviewText: This blends like butter into my cream foundation and cc cream. Its buildable so start light to find the look you hope to achieve. I have battled with this whole contour thing for years. I've tried pricey solid sticks, powders, and concealers but this budget friendly little guy beats them all! I should add that I don't use any type of powder on my face so I can't speak to how it will blend or look if powder is used.

reviews.reviewerName: Here in the Ninth Ring of Hell
reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just wow! The first contour I really, really love for fair skin
reviews.reviewText: I have not been able to establish a satisfying relationship with a contour until now. In the winter I'm VERY fair, and my skin is neutral in tone and things seem to oxidize warm on me after application so finding makeup products that don't end up orangey or muddy or weird is an uphill process. This product, however, is a delight. No orange cast that makes it look like I'm trying too hard to look tan in winter, sheer and blendable as can be, the texture is really lovely and it carries just enough pigment to create the most natural shadow contour. The sponge tip offers more precision than any other product I've used, and the tiny hint of jowling I've developed is thankful for that; nothing's ever going to make it look like my jawline is snatched, but it makes it so that's not the first thing that draws the eye. Honestly, this product has impressed me so much that I'm really motivated to try the Halo Glow blush and highlighter as well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good color for fair skin (not orange-y) but disappointing
reviews.reviewText: It's a bit challenging to blend this product without wiping it off. I'm still experimenting, and I think the trick will be to apply it in various places and then go back to blend it once it has 30 seconds or so to set first. I got this based on the positive reviews to see if I could find a less pricey alternative to Anastasia but I'll either try something else or go back to it. Also, as one reviewed posted in a pic, there's a weird connection between the tube and the sponge applicator that oozes a small amount of the product. Seems like poor packaging.In spite of all that, the fair/light color is great for my complexion because it provides a shadow without looking the least bit orange-toned.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This product is amazing, I ordered it in fair/light, the color is very cool tones just like the product says so it’s more of a contour than a bronzer, the other shades seem to look more like a bronzer and very warm toned. I loved the product so much and I use it everyday. I would definitely recommend buying it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This product lives up to the hype!
reviews.reviewText: Beautiful color and buttery feel. Don’t pay the high prices of the high end products when this is just as nice. I will definitely be purchasing again. You will not be disappointed if you try it.

This is my new favorite contour. It goes on very easy with the sponge applicator. You can be very precise in where you put it. The consistency is very similar to liquid foundation. It blends really well and the color is perfect for my skin tone. I am quite pale and I like a darker contour. This suits me very well. I expected to go though it very quickly but a little goes a long way. I have used it daily for 3 months now. I will definitely buy again. I love elf products and their halo glow line is a hit for me.

I am super fair, like glow in the dark fair and contour creams/powders have always been tough because they're generally warmer colours and it makes it look like I have hideous self tanner on my face. I love this contour cream in fair/light, it cool toned, blends easy and a little goes along way. My fair ladies you won't be disappointed!

I got the light/medium and it was way too dark on my skin. I am fair/light with more of an olive undertone, but I got this shade because reviews said the fair was grey looking and cool toned. Seems like a good product though, was a nice consistency and blended well
Super easy to use and blend, good price

reviews.reviewTitle: Happy with product, worth the purchase
reviews.reviewText: Great product and brand - However, a bit pricey for the size. Product is light and doesn't feel heavy. Worth the purchase!
